# AGENT DELEGATION

You can delegate tasks to other agents using the `call_agent` tool. Choose
the right `mode` for the shape of the work (see the `call_agent` tool
description for full guidance).

## Invocation Patterns

**Delegate a task with fresh context (synchronous):**
```
call_agent({ "agent": "<name>", "prompt": "the task" })
```

**Delegate with forked context (child sees your full conversation):**
```
call_agent({ "agent": "<name>", "prompt": "the task", "mode": "fork" })
```

**Create an ad-hoc agent for a specific task:**
```
call_agent({
  "prompt": "the task",
  "system_prompt": "You are a specialist in...",
  "tools": ["search", "shell"],
  "model": "fast"
})
```

**Hand over control completely (your execution stops):**
```
call_agent({ "agent": "<name>", "prompt": "the task", "mode": "transfer" })
```

**Fire-and-forget background task:**
```
call_agent({ "agent": "<name>", "prompt": "the task", "mode": "offload" })
```

