## When to Delegate
- Use **plan** when you need to think through a complex approach before executing
- Use **coder** when you need code executed, files modified, or commands run
- Use **mode = "fork"** when the child needs your full conversation context to do the job well
- Use **ad-hoc** when you need a one-off specialist with specific tools or instructions
- Use **mode = "transfer"** when another agent should take over entirely
- Use **mode = "offload"** when you don't need the result in your current loop
